type

String type
Holds the range type. Typically following range types are known:
  • between
  • equal
  • greaterthan
  • greaterthanequal
  • lessthan
  • lessthanequal
  • match
  • notequal
  • notmatch

Method Detail

write

private void write(Appendable _out)
            throws IOException
Write this range value to the writer instance. Following range types are converted:
  • "equal" to "="
  • "greaterthan" to ">"
  • "greaterthanequal" to ">="
  • "lessthan" to "<"
  • "lessthanequal" to "<="
  • "notequal" to "!="
  • "notmatch" to "!match"
  • "notsmatch" to "!smatch"
If the range type is a program, the name of the program and the input arguments are defined directly on the attribute in AbstractAttribute_mxJPO.rangeProgramRef and AbstractAttribute_mxJPO.rangeProgramInputArguments.

Parameters:
_out - writer instance
Throws:
IOException - if write to the writer instance is not possible

remove4Update

private void remove4Update(Appendable _out)
                    throws IOException
Appends the MQL code to remove this range depending on the type of range in type. If it is a program the related name of program is defined as attribute variable in AbstractAttribute_mxJPO.rangeProgramRef.

Parameters:
_out - appendable instance where the MQL code is appended to remove this range
Throws:
IOException - if the MQL code could not appended

compareTo

public int compareTo(AbstractAttribute_mxJPO.Range _range)
Compare this range instance with given range instance. The compare is done for each instance variable in this order:
  • type
  • include1
  • include2
  • value1
  • value2
If one of the compared instance variables are not equal, the compared value is returned. So only if all instance variable has the same values the ranges itself are identically.

Specified by:
compareTo in interface Comparable<AbstractAttribute_mxJPO.Range>
Parameters:
_range - range instance to which this instance must be compared to
Returns:
"0" if both ranges are equal; "1" if greater; otherwise "-1"
